| AvoidKeepCpuOn.java:46:36:46:97 | newWakeLock(...) | PowerManager.newWakeLock() is called with a screen-affecting wake lock level (SCREEN_DIM_WAKE_LOCK, SCREEN_BRIGHT_WAKE_LOCK, or FULL_WAKE_LOCK). This keeps the screen on and significantly drains battery. If only CPU is needed, use PARTIAL_WAKE_LOCK instead. |
